<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>The Limit of Human Felicity</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --paper: #f3ead7;
    --paper-warm: #fbf4e6;
    --ink: #191713;
    --muted: #756b5f;
    --line: #d4c3a7;
    --blue: #154f65;
    --red: #b74735;
    --gold: #d79b2d;
    --green: #687d50;
    --shadow: rgba(44, 33, 22, .18);
    --sans: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
    --serif: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", Palatino, Georgia, serif;
  }

  * {
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  html {
    scroll-behavior: smooth;
  }

  body {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    background:
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(25, 23, 19, .045) 1px, transparent 1px) 0 0 / 48px 48px,
      linear-gradient(180deg, var(--paper-warm), var(--paper));
  }

  body::before {
    content: "";
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: -1;
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: .32;
    background-image: radial-gradient(rgba(25, 23, 19, .18) .55px, transparent .55px);
    background-size: 13px 13px;
  }

  button {
    font: inherit;
  }

  img {
    display: block;
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .skip-link {
    position: absolute;
    left: 1rem;
    top: 1rem;
    z-index: 30;
    transform: translateY(-180%);
    padding: .5rem .7rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    background: var(--paper-warm);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: .85rem;
  }

  .skip-link:focus {
    transform: translateY(0);
  }

  .site-header {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    z-index: 20;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: .8rem clamp(1rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    color: rgba(25, 23, 19, .72);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: .72rem;
    font-weight: 750;
    letter-spacing: .12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    transform: translateY(-1rem);
    transition: opacity .2s ease, transform .2s ease;
  }

  body.is-story-header .site-header {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }

  .hero {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    isolation: isolate;
    min-height: 92svh;
    display: grid;
    align-items: end;
    padding: 5.5rem clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem) 2rem;
  }

  .hero-grid {
    position: relative;
    width: min(1500px, 100%);
    margin: 0 auto;
    min-height: min(680px, 76svh);
    display: grid;
    align-items: end;
  }

  .hero-grid > div {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    max-width: 38rem;
  }

  .rail-year,
  .ledger-kicker {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--red);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: .72rem;
    font-weight: 820;
  }

  .rail-year {
    letter-spacing: .14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .ledger-kicker {
    letter-spacing: .05em;
    text-transform: none;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  h1 {
    max-width: 8.8ch;
    margin: 0 0 1.15rem;
    font-size: 7.7rem;
    font-weight: 520;
    line-height: .88;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .dek {
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: #4c443b;
    font-size: 1.28rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .hero-art {
    position: absolute;
    z-index: 1;
    inset: 7% -4% 4rem 34%;
    margin: 0;
    opacity: .12;
    pointer-events: none;
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
  }

  .hero-art::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: -4%;
    right: 10%;
    bottom: -1.2rem;
    height: 16%;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--shadow);
    filter: blur(18px);
  }

  .hero-art::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--paper-warm) 0%, rgba(251, 244, 230, .78) 23%, rgba(251, 244, 230, 0) 55%);
  }

  .hero-art img {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: 0;
    object-fit: contain;
    object-position: right bottom;
    box-shadow: none;
    filter: saturate(.9) contrast(.95);
  }

  .route-note {
    width: min(1500px, calc(100% - 2rem));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1rem 0 1.35rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    color: #8a5a48;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: .8rem;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: .68rem;
    font-weight: 760;
    letter-spacing: .16em;
    line-height: 1.45;
    text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .route-note::before,
  .route-note::after {
    content: "";
    width: clamp(1.4rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, rgba(138, 90, 72, .48));
  }

  .route-note::after {
    background: linear-gradient(to left, transparent, rgba(138, 90, 72, .48));
  }

  .chapter {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.03fr) minmax(330px, .78fr);
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 4rem);
    width: min(1500px, calc(100% - 2rem));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem) 0 clamp(4rem, 8vw, 8rem);
  }

  .room-stage {
    position: sticky;
    top: clamp(2.5rem, 6vh, 4.5rem);
    align-self: start;
  }

  .room-frame {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    aspect-ratio: 1.58;
    height: auto;
    min-height: 0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(25, 23, 19, .22);
    background: #eadcc2;
    box-shadow: 0 18px 60px rgba(44, 33, 22, .15);
  }

  .image-plane,
  .hotspot-plane {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    transform-origin: 0 0;
    will-change: transform;
    transition: transform .62s cubic-bezier(.2, .78, .2, 1);
  }

  .image-plane {
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .image-plane img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: fill;
    filter: brightness(1.04) saturate(1.02) contrast(.99);
  }

  .hotspot-plane {
    z-index: 4;
    pointer-events: none;
  }


  .focus-wash {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 2;
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: .72;
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at var(--spot-x, 50%) var(--spot-y, 50%), rgba(255, 239, 190, .18) 0 9%, rgba(255, 240, 204, .08) 18%, rgba(255, 248, 226, 0) 32%),
      radial-gradient(circle at var(--spot-x, 50%) var(--spot-y, 50%), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0) 0 38%, rgba(55, 43, 31, .035) 70%, rgba(55, 43, 31, .07) 100%);
    transition: background .35s ease;
    mix-blend-mode: normal;
  }

  .hotspots {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 4;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .hotspot {
    --accent: var(--gold);
    position: absolute;
    left: var(--x);
    top: var(--y);
    width: .72rem;
    height: .72rem;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(25, 23, 19, .42);
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(251, 244, 230, .76);
    color: var(--ink);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(251, 244, 230, .46);
    cursor: pointer;
    pointer-events: auto;
    transition: transform .18s ease, background .18s ease, box-shadow .18s ease;
  }

  .hotspot::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: -.38rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: inherit;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: scale(.7);
    transition: opacity .18s ease, transform .18s ease;
  }

  .hotspot span {
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    bottom: calc(100% + .42rem);
    width: max-content;
    max-width: 8.5rem;
    transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(.18rem);
    padding: .24rem .42rem .26rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(116, 96, 70, .24);
    border-radius: 999px;
    color: #4e4439;
    background: rgba(250, 241, 223, .88);
    box-shadow: 0 .28rem .85rem rgba(44, 33, 22, .13);
    backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: .62rem;
    font-weight: 650;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: .03em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    transition: opacity .18s ease, transform .18s ease;
  }

  .hotspot:hover,
  .hotspot:focus-visible,
  .hotspot.is-active {
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1.14);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(251, 244, 230, .92);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(251, 244, 230, .78), 0 4px 12px rgba(44, 33, 22, .14);
    outline: 0;
  }

  .hotspot:hover::before,
  .hotspot:focus-visible::before,
  .hotspot.is-active::before {
    opacity: .45;
    transform: scale(1.22);
  }

  .hotspot:hover span,
  .hotspot:focus-visible span,
  .hotspot.is-active span {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(0);
  }

  .stage-caption {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: .75rem 0 0;
    color: #5d5348;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: .78rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }

  .active-mini {
    color: var(--red);
    font-weight: 820;
    letter-spacing: .08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .story-column {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .step {
    min-height: 78vh;
    display: grid;
    align-content: center;
    padding: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6.5rem) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .step.is-active .item-title {
    color: var(--blue);
  }

  .item-title {
    margin: 0 0 .9rem;
    font-size: 3.35rem;
    font-weight: 520;
    line-height: .98;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    transition: color .2s ease;
  }

  .quote {
    margin: 0;
    color: #211e19;
    font-size: 1.42rem;
    line-height: 1.32;
  }

  .quote::before {
    content: open-quote;
    color: var(--red);
  }

  .quote::after {
    content: close-quote;
    color: var(--red);
  }

  .source {
    margin: .9rem 0 0;
    color: #655749;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: .86rem;
    font-weight: 650;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }

  .context {
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    color: #4f453a;
    font-size: 1.03rem;
    line-height: 1.58;
  }

  .rail {
    position: sticky;
    bottom: 0;
    z-index: 10;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(25, 23, 19, .18);
    background: rgba(251, 244, 230, .88);
    backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
  }

  .rail-inner {
    width: min(1500px, calc(100% - 2rem));
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-auto-flow: column;
    grid-auto-columns: minmax(7.5rem, 1fr);
    gap: .3rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    padding: .55rem 0;
  }

  .rail-button {
    min-height: 3.45rem;
    border: 0;
    border-left: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: .25rem .6rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    background: transparent;
    text-align: left;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .rail-button:hover,
  .rail-button:focus-visible,
  .rail-button.is-active {
    background: rgba(183, 71, 53, .09);
    outline: none;
  }

  .rail-label {
    display: block;
    margin-top: .16rem;
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: .88rem;
    font-weight: 520;
    line-height: 1.08;
  }

  .ledger {
    width: min(1240px, calc(100% - 2rem));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink);
  }

  .ledger-head {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, .7fr) minmax(280px, .5fr);
    gap: clamp(1.4rem, 4vw, 4rem);
    align-items: end;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .ledger h2 {
    max-width: 9ch;
    margin: .55rem 0 0;
    font-size: 4.8rem;
    font-weight: 520;
    line-height: .86;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .ledger-copy {
    margin: 0;
    color: #4f453a;
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .ledger-note {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    color: #756b5f;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: .78rem;
    letter-spacing: .08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .ledger-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-left: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .ledger-item {
    min-height: 11.5rem;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: .9rem;
    background: rgba(251, 244, 230, .48);
  }

  .ledger-item h3 {
    margin: .5rem 0 .65rem;
    font-size: 1.42rem;
    font-weight: 540;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .ledger-item p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #51473d;
    font-size: .98rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    html {
      scroll-behavior: auto;
    }

    .focus-wash,
    .hotspot,
    .hotspot::before,
    .image-plane,
    .hotspot-plane,
    .hotspot span,
    .item-title {
      transition: none;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 1050px) {
    .hero-grid,
    .chapter,
    .ledger-head {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .hero {
      min-height: auto;
      padding-top: 5.5rem;
    }

    .room-stage {
      position: relative;
      top: auto;
    }

    .room-frame {
      aspect-ratio: 1.58;
      height: auto;
      min-height: 0;
    }

    .step {
      min-height: auto;
      padding: 3.4rem 0;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .site-header {
      display: none;
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 2rem 1rem 1rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 4.15rem;
      line-height: .92;
    }

    .hero-grid {
      gap: 1.4rem;
    }

    .hero-art {
      display: none;
    }

    .hero-art img,
    .room-frame {
      border-left: 0;
      border-right: 0;
    }

    .chapter {
      width: 100%;
      padding-top: 1rem;
    }

    .story-column,
    .stage-caption {
      width: calc(100% - 2rem);
      margin-left: auto;
      margin-right: auto;
    }

    .hotspot {
      width: .62rem;
      height: .62rem;
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(251, 244, 230, .62);
    }

    .hotspot span {
      display: none;
    }

    .ledger-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .rail-inner {
      width: calc(100% - 1rem);
    }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<a class="skip-link" href="#story">Skip to story</a>
<header class="site-header" aria-hidden="true">
  <span>The Limit of Human Felicity</span>
</header>

<main>
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="title">
    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div>
        <h1 id="title">Everyday Utopia</h1>
        <p class="dek">Edward Bellamy once imagined music on demand and said it would be "the limit of human felicity." A modern apartment is full of things that once drew the same kind of awe.</p>
      </div>
      <figure class="hero-art">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="1672" height="941" alt="An editorial illustration of a modern apartment with everyday objects including a speaker, lamp, books, refrigerator, faucet, medicine cabinet, washing machine, and bicycle.">
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>
  <p class="route-note">scroll to move through the apartment</p>

  <section class="chapter" id="story" aria-label="Stories of everyday abundance">
    <div class="room-stage" aria-label="Interactive illustrated room">
      <div class="room-frame">
        <div class="image-plane" id="imagePlane">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="1672" height="941" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="focus-wash" id="focusWash" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="hotspot-plane" id="hotspotPlane">
          <div class="hotspots" id="hotspots"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-caption">
        <span class="active-mini" id="activeMini">Any song, at home</span>
        <span id="activeSource">Edward Bellamy, 1888</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="story-column">
      <div id="steps"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <nav class="rail" aria-label="Jump between household objects">
    <div class="rail-inner" id="rail"></div>
  </nav>

  <section class="ledger" aria-labelledby="ledger-title">
    <div class="ledger-head">
      <div>
        <h2 id="ledger-title">What wonder becomes.</h2>
        <p class="ledger-note">Availability timeline</p>
      </div>
      <p class="ledger-copy">The hard part is not noticing a new marvel. It is remembering it after it has become furniture.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ledger-grid" id="ledger"></div>
  </section>
</main>

<script>
const ITEMS = [
  {
    id: "music",
    title: "Any song, at home",
    object: "Speaker",
    then: "Recorded music",
    year: "1888",
    availableYear: "1890s",
    availableSort: 1892,
    who: "Edward Bellamy",
    quote: "If we could have devised an arrangement for providing everybody with music in their homes, perfect in quality, unlimited in quantity, suited to every mood, and beginning and ceasing at will, we should have considered the limit of human felicity already attained.",
    source: "Looking Backward, imagining the impossible future of the year 2000.",
    context: "Before recorded music and radio, hearing music on demand meant having instruments or performers nearby. Most listening was tied to live performance, place, and schedule.",
    x: 16,
    y: 60,
    color: "#d79b2d"
  },
  {
    id: "light",
    title: "Light without flame",
    object: "Lamp",
    then: "Electric light",
    year: "1880",
    availableYear: "1882",
    availableSort: 1882,
    who: "A witness at Wabash, Indiana",
    quote: "The strange, weird light, exceeded in power only by the sun, rendered the square as light as midday ... we contemplated the new wonder of science, as lightning was brought down from the heavens.",
    source: "The night the first city on earth was lit by electric light.",
    context: "Before electric lighting, households relied on candles, oil lamps, gaslight, or daylight. Evening work was dimmer, smokier, and more fire-prone.",
    x: 10,
    y: 58,
    color: "#d79b2d"
  },
  {
    id: "painting",
    title: "A museum on the wall",
    object: "Painting",
    then: "Art reproductions",
    year: "1947",
    availableYear: "1860s",
    availableSort: 1865,
    who: "Andre Malraux",
    quote: "A museum without walls has been opened to us, and it will carry infinitely farther that limited revelation of the world of art which the real museums offer us within their walls.",
    source: "Le Musee imaginaire, later translated as The Museum Without Walls.",
    context: "Before reliable reproduction, most people saw major artworks only by visiting churches, collections, or museums. Prints and photographs made artworks portable and widely comparable.",
    x: 15,
    y: 38,
    color: "#154f65"
  },
  {
    id: "photo",
    title: "A face kept",
    object: "Photograph",
    then: "Photography",
    year: "1843",
    availableYear: "1839",
    availableSort: 1839,
    who: "Elizabeth Barrett Browning",
    quote: "The very shadow of the person lying there fixed for ever! ... I would rather have such a memorial of one I dearly loved, than the noblest artist's work ever produced.",
    source: "On first seeing a daguerreotype, in a letter to Mary Russell Mitford.",
    context: "Before photography, preserving a likeness usually required a painted portrait, which was expensive and slow. Many families had no accurate image of relatives who died.",
    x: 20,
    y: 61,
    color: "#b74735"
  },
  {
    id: "glasses",
    title: "Reading after the eyes fail",
    object: "Eyeglasses",
    then: "Corrected vision",
    year: "1306",
    availableYear: "c. 1286",
    availableSort: 1286,
    who: "Friar Giordano da Pisa",
    quote: "It is not twenty years since there was discovered the art of making spectacles ... one of the best and most necessary in the world. I myself saw the man who discovered it, and I talked with him.",
    source: "A sermon at Santa Maria Novella, Florence.",
    context: "Before spectacles, age-related vision loss could end reading, sewing, and other close work. Corrective lenses extended those tasks into later life.",
    x: 24,
    y: 60,
    color: "#154f65"
  },
  {
    id: "phone",
    title: "A message sent instantly",
    object: "Phone",
    then: "Instant communication",
    year: "1858",
    availableYear: "1878",
    availableSort: 1878,
    who: "Briggs & Maverick",
    quote: "Of all the marvellous achievements of modern science, the Electric Telegraph is transcendently the greatest and most serviceable to mankind. It is a perpetual miracle, which no familiarity can render commonplace.",
    source: "The Story of the Telegraph.",
    context: "Before telegraphy and telephony, messages traveled no faster than a courier, horse, ship, or train. Long-distance communication could take days, weeks, or months.",
    x: 27,
    y: 77,
    color: "#154f65"
  },
  {
    id: "fruit",
    title: "The rented pineapple",
    object: "Pineapple",
    then: "Imported fruit",
    year: "1822",
    availableYear: "1820s",
    availableSort: 1820,
    who: "Charles Lamb",
    quote: "Like lovers' kisses, she biteth, she is a pleasure bordering on pain, from the fierceness and insanity of her relish.",
    source: "On the rapture of the pineapple.",
